150. Python Security Best Practices ⭐
Practices used to make Python applications secure.
Python security best practices include validating user input, avoiding unsafe functions such as eval(), using parameterized database queries, protecting secrets, and keeping dependencies updated.

Avoid eval()
In Python, eval() is a built-in function that dynamically parses, compiles, and executes a string as a Python expression
You must avoid it for security practices because it creates arbitrary code execution (ACE) vulnerabilities, allowing attackers to run malicious commands directly on your system

